scail-2-mlx-swift
Copyright 2026 xocialize

Apple MLX port of SCAIL-2. Derived from:

- SCAIL-2 (https://github.com/zai-org/SCAIL-2), Zhipu AI / zai-org,
  Apache-2.0. Model architecture (wan/modules/model_scail2.py), pipeline
  (wan/scail.py), mask utilities, and checkpoint key remapping (convert.py)
  are translated 1:1 from this codebase.
- Wan2.1 (https://github.com/Wan-Video/Wan2.1), Alibaba Wan Team,
  Apache-2.0. SCAIL-2 is a fork of the Wan2.1 codebase; the VAE, umT5
  encoder, and CLIP modules originate there.
- mlx-video (https://github.com/Blaizzy/mlx-video), Prince Canuma,
  MIT. Provides the Wan2 MLX substrate used at runtime (WanVAE, T5Encoder,
  FlowUniPCScheduler).
- CLIP / open_clip (OpenAI / mlfoundations), MIT. The xlm-roberta ViT-H/14
  visual tower architecture.

Model weights converted from https://huggingface.co/zai-org/SCAIL-2
(model card states MIT; the GitHub repository is Apache-2.0).
